SIMPLE: erst
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erst
<hw>Erst</hw> <pr>(⟦etil⟧rst)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Orig.
superlative of <ets>ere</ets>; AS. <ets>⟦aemac⟧rest</ets>. See
<er>Ere</er>.]</ety> <mark>[Archaic]</mark> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>First.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Previously; before; formerly; heretofore.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Tityrus, with whose style he had <qex>erst</qex> disclaimed all
ambition to match his pastoral pipe.</q> <rj><qau>A. W.
Ward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>At erst</b></col>, <cd>at first; at the beginning.</cd>
-- <col><b>Now at erst</b></col>, <cd>at this present time.</cd>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erstwhile</ent>⟦br⟧
